      "writtenOn": "2026-03-19T13:28:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This currently compares against `//:release.war.jars.txt`, which pulls in `//plugins:core` and therefore requires all core plugin submodules to be present during Bazel analysis.\n\nIn Zuul CI Gerrit is intentionally cloned without core plugin submodules. As a result, this change breaks verification with errors like:\n\n```\nno such package \u0027plugins/...\u0027\n```\n\nThis is not specific to this plugin, but a general consequence of using the release WAR as the comparison target.\n\nFor this check, we only need to compare against jars provided by Gerrit itself—not those coming from packaged core plugins.\n\nUsing: `//:headless.war.jars.txt` provides exactly that scope and avoids introducing unnecessary dependencies on core plugin submodules.\n\nI was able to reproduce the failure locally by cloning Gerrit without submodules, and switching to `headless.war.jars.txt` resolves the issue while preserving the intent of the check.\n\n`against` target should be changed accordingly to: //:headless.war.jars.txt`.",
